data.text/markdown:
canvod-readers Examples

GNSS data format readers for the canVODpy ecosystem. This package provides readers for various GNSS data formats, with a focus on RINEX v3.04 observation files.

Installation

uv pip install canvod-readers
For development: 
git clone https://github.com/nfb2021/canvodpy.git
cd canvodpy
uv sync
Import the Package

Reading RINEX v3.04 Files

The main class for reading RINEX v3.04 observation files is Rnxv3Obs. It automatically parses the header and validates the file structure.

console.name: stdout
console.text:
✓ Successfully loaded: rref001a00.25o
✓ RINEX version: 3.04
✓ Marker name: rref
✓ Systems: M

data.text/markdown:
Header Information

The RINEX header contains important metadata about the observation file.

console.name: stdout
console.text:
Header Information:
  Observer: NFB
  Agency: CLIMERS@TUW
  Receiver: SEPT ASTERX SB3
  Antenna: Unknown
  Position: [<Quantity(4127831.95, 'meter')>, <Quantity(1207193.37, 'meter')>, <Quantity(4695247.2, 'meter')>]
  First observation: {'UTC': datetime.datetime(2024, 12, 31, 23, 59, 42, tzinfo=<UTC>), 'GPS': datetime.datetime(2025, 1, 1, 0, 0)}
